UPDATE LocalizedText SET Text = "Tribal Villages are less civilized than other civilizations, but are friendly nonetheless. Visiting tribal villages provide a random benefit to the civilization of the unit that first enters their tile. The village disappears after its gifts have been claimed. Gifts include survivors, such as Builders or Traders, technology or technology boosts, military units, [ICON_Faith] Faith, [ICON_Gold] Gold, [ICON_GreatWork_Relic] Relics, or civic boosts.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE] If by chance you stumble upon a wondrous tribal village, your benefits include a random unit or improvement from any civilization, a random resource or policy, wilderness training, a meeting with an unmet city-state, knowledge of an undiscovered wonder, or a formation upgrade." WHERE Tag = 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WORLD_5_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1';